{0 Hover}

Show a preview of the link target's content on hover.

{1 Input}

A cursor position (0-based line and character) in a markdown file that
belongs to a vault with a built index.

{1 Link detection}

Same link forms as {!page-"feature-go-to-definition"}: wikilinks,
markdown links, markdown images.  External URLs are excluded.

{1 Response}

If the cursor falls on a recognized link, return a
[textDocument/hover] response:

{t
  | Field          | Value                                            |
  |----------------|--------------------------------------------------|
  | contents       | Markdown string (see below)                      |
  | range          | byte range of the link                           |
}

{2 Contents format}

The hover content is a Markdown string with [MarkupKind.Markdown].

{ul
  {- {b Resolved note / file link} ([[[note]]]): the raw markdown
     content of the target file.}
  {- {b Resolved heading fragment} ([[[note#Heading]]]): the markdown
     content of the section starting at the matched heading, up to (but
     not including) the next heading of equal or higher level.}
  {- {b Resolved block-ID fragment} ([[[note#^blockid]]]): the
     paragraph that carries the block ID.}
  {- {b Self-referencing fragments} ([[[#Heading]]], [[[#^blockid]]]):
     same as above but sourced from the current file.}
  {- {b Unresolved link}: no hover result (return [None]).}
}

{2 Truncation}

If the content string exceeds {!Lsp_config.t.hover_max_chars} bytes,
it is truncated at that boundary (snapped to the previous newline to
avoid cutting mid-word) and the suffix ["\n\n*(truncated)*"] is
appended.

{1 Edge cases}

{ul
  {- {b Cursor outside any link}: no hover result.}
  {- {b Target file unreadable}: no hover result.}
  {- {b Heading / block not found in target file}: fall back to the full
     file content (subject to truncation), consistent with the
     go-to-definition fallback.}
}
